Made some more for myself while stuck inside during the blizzard...since they're so easy to make. ^-^
Here's the pillows I made for John... I posted them in my other journal but I wanted them in here too since it's the 'stuff I've made' journal haha.

Here's 2 pictures I've done on photoshop... ...a flamingo again... ...and a forest with an owl & a bunny... I did this in class, and never really did much else with it because we had to pick a certain setting... and I didn't have much of an inspiration to work on this.
Now for some older stuff! Annnd, now for some silly little things I've done!

Fishy & rainbow coral! The sun chasing after bunnies to eat! A turtle eating cheeerios! Purple & Pink fairy Chat Noir Crabmonsters This is part of the fish in the 'crabmonsters' painting... I saved it cause I liked it so much! hehehe Kemushi A Flamingo on the beach Happy Breakfast! Iguanarama Mermaid & a puffer fish (cause John said he liked those fishies, hehe) My version of the Lucky Charms... minus the red balloon & pot of gold... I got bored with this and stopped working on it! Aw.. It's Mr.Octopus! And likes to eat popcorn... but what's this? The popcorn... it looks like baby octopusses? Oh no! Not sure why I did this one... but it's kinda cute & fluffy so here it is... Princess kissing a Froggy... how original haha... I thought she looked like a neon light sign. Quickly drawn... It's of me & John when we went out to dinner at Mandarin Court for Valentine's Day 2004. ^-^ A Sad 3 of Hearts... because he's got a tear in his cardness... hehe I got this idea while drawing another crab picture... and thought I'd draw a crab w/rubberbands on his claws... and make them like hand cuffs!

*This is, from now on, my alternate journal! My other one is chococatfaerie... this one I will use to post my art or pictures that I really want to show to people in communities or just friends or anyone who stumbles onto this journal! I'm going to try to post pictures on here as often as I can... hopefully I don't forget I even have this new journal! haha I figured that I'd start of the new year with a new journal. But, not forgetting my old one!*
